><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 5:26 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I made an Erudite SK when Paineel came out, cause that was the thing to so at the time ;o) <br>I gave her points in Str and Int.&nbsp;&nbsp;I stripped her at level 9 and left her camped in EC for a few months, cause I was tired of having her constantly be encumbered.  Having only 80 STR on a Tank character is not too bright eh?<br>Well, since the leveling of the Mana pool, I went and rewtinked her with Bronze and few items.  her str is now up to 100.  Int is at 130 or so.  I have her at level 11, and I am Very impressed with her now.<br>At 12, My Bard was getting his butt handed to him by Fire Drakes and Blue Dervs.  At 12 My Enchanter could do a little better, but not without exhausting his mana pool.  At 11 the SK can wallop the daylights oout of them, and be at half mana and half life. <br>SKs are Excellent Solo classes, at least at this level.<br>And we surely can kick some tail in a group also.<br>For some ungoldy reason, I was in a group with all SKs.  2 level 10s, a level 11, and a level 12.<br>We pulled everything to the Najena Zone in Lavastorm.  Let me tell you, with 4 of us swinging, lifetapping, and having out tiny pets atacking, we were a virtual blender of death.<br>  We took on Drakes, Elementals and Imps one after another in a constant stream.  Once we had to stop pulling and heal, cause the puller went extra far for an Imp, who DOTd him all the way back.<br>Im telling you, at 9-15, the old Disease, Siphon, Liftap combo, works wonders, and USE A PET!!  They may not do much damage, but at the very least, they will give you a few extra seconds to Zone.<br>I have a new favorite character now, I may regret my piss poor stamina and low str later on, but for now, I am having a blast!<br><br>Sapper 25 Bard<br>Elddirbob 13 Enchanter<br>Katrinah 11 ShadowKnight.<br>&nbsp;<br>Sapper Diesalot, At Deaths Door.&nbsp;&nbsp;"Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></tr>
