<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96731190729109></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96731190729109><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=96731190729109>RE: Erudite SKs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=96731190729109#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 26th 1:45 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am currently a level 9 Erudite SK.&nbsp;&nbsp;I was the ultimate tank in Tox. Forest, I soloed entire kobold camps (an easy feat!) and killed the skeletons, abandoned heretic pets until level 7.  Then I got fed up of being slaughtered by the wandering elemental and I tried my hand at going through Quenos to get to Freeport.  I found out the stationary guards are not KOS, but the wandering guards will attack.  After a failed attempt to get through the sewers (I got severly lost and killed), I was lucky enough to find a great druid to teleport me to Freeport.  I am now level 9 and I can solo things in EC that con yellow to me.  My paladin friend/slave tells me that he could never solo even white monsters!  SKs are the best solo class and work even better in a group.  They are even more fun to role play (especially against newbies! HeHe.)  My erudite INT of a natural 117 is now 125 when I am fully armed.  My STR is 97 and my STA and AGI are not that bad either, in fact my lowest stat is CHA at 75!  I have one thing to say to everyone considering making a erudite SK, go for it!  Level as much as possible in Tox, you'll now when it is time to leave, then get to Freeport.<br><br>Uzlan 9 ShadowKnight (Morell-Thule)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
